1️⃣ TYPICAL PLACEMENT PROCESS (Most Companies)

Usually 4 stages:

Round 1 — Aptitude Test

Tests:

Quantitative aptitude
Logical reasoning
Verbal ability

(You’ve covered these ✅)

Example Companies:
Tata Consultancy Services (TCS NQT style)
Infosys
Accenture
2️⃣ ROUND 2 — CODING / TECHNICAL SCREEN

Common tasks:

Basic programming logic
SQL queries
OOP basics
DSA basics (sometimes easy/medium)

Typical questions:

Reverse a string
Find largest number
Basic joins in SQL
Difference between stack and queue

👉 Many service companies ask moderate-level coding, not extreme DSA.

3️⃣ ROUND 3 — TECHNICAL INTERVIEW

Questions often include:

HR + Technical Mix:
Tell me about yourself
Explain a project
What is OOP?
What is DBMS?
Why should we hire you?
4️⃣ ROUND 4 — HR INTERVIEW

Topics:

Relocation
Bond
Strengths/Weaknesses
Salary expectations

(We already trained this ✅)

🔹 COMPANY PATTERN EXAMPLES
🟦 TCS-type pattern

Often:

Aptitude + verbal
Coding (sometimes)
Interview

Focus:

Accuracy
Communication
Consistency
🟨 Infosys-type pattern

Often includes:

Aptitude
Puzzles
Technical + HR

Focus:

Reasoning
Communication
Fundamentals
🟩 Accenture-type pattern

Often includes:

Cognitive assessment
Technical assessment
Communication assessment

Focus:

Aptitude + spoken English
5️⃣ ELIMINATION HAPPENS MOSTLY BECAUSE OF:

❌ Poor communication
❌ Panic in aptitude
❌ Weak project explanation
❌ Bad HR answers

Not always because of hard technical questions.

